  "time_ut": 1660701960,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0dcf\u0d9c\u0db8\u0dca 7\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0da7  \u0d9c\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0d9c\u0db8\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dbb 56\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "7 airlines reduce 56 flights per week",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Due to the lack of fueling facilities and revenue generation problems, 7 foreign airlines have reduced the number of flights to Sri Lanka from 108 to 52 in a week by 56 flights.",
        "It is reported that 5 airlines have reduced the number of flights and 02 airlines have even stopped coming to Sri Lanka.",
        "It is reported that Emirates, Qatar Airways, Etihad, Oman, Air India have reduced the number of flights to Sri Lanka and Saudi Air and Kuwait Airways have suspended their flights to Sri Lanka.",
        "Emirates airlines used to operate 26 flights a week and they have reduced it to 14 now. Qatar Airways previously operated 35 flights per week, which has now been reduced to 31.",
        "Etihad previously operated 14 flights per week and has now reduced it to 06.",
        "Oman Airlines previously operated 11 flights per week and has now reduced it to 07. Air India previously operated 09 flights per week and reduced it to 04 due to weak demand.",
        "Also, Saudi Air, which operated 07 flights per week, and Kuwait Airways, which operated 04 flights per week, have suspended flights to Sri Lanka.",
        "It is also reported that Maldives, Korean, Salam Airways, Thai Smile, Vistara, China Southern and Swiss International have restricted their operations with the country until the situation in the country improves."
      ],
